# Local Docker + Kubernetes Deployment (Tailscale HA)

Learned knowledge from live deployments on this machine. Apply whenever working with Docker Compose, Kubernetes, or Tailscale networking in this repo.

---

## Environment Layout

**This machine**: `mayank-mbp25` · Tailscale IP `100.79.214.33` · Role: primary (DB node)

Two-layer stack:

| Layer | Tool | Services | Persistence |
|-------|------|----------|-------------|
| Infra | Docker Compose (`infra/docker/docker-compose.dev.yml`) | postgres, redis, prometheus, grafana, mailhog, localstack | Named volumes + `restart: unless-stopped` |
| Apps | Kubernetes (docker-desktop context) | api-gateway, auth-service, clinical-engine, data-pipeline, ai-inference, notification-service | K8s auto-restarts pods |

Both layers must be running for the stack to work. Infra must start before K8s pods.

---

## One-Command Flows

### First machine (primary — hosts postgres/redis for the whole Tailscale cluster)
```bash
make docker-up && make k8s-install-primary
```

### Every additional machine (secondary — on Tailscale)
```bash
make docker-up && bash scripts/bootstrap/install-k8s.sh --db-host 100.79.214.33
```
Replace `100.79.214.33` with the primary machine's Tailscale IP.

### Clean reinstall (any machine, keeps Docker volumes)
```bash
make k8s-reinstall
```

### Full nuclear reset (wipes all data)
```bash
make k8s-uninstall && make docker-down
bash scripts/seed.sh --reset
make docker-up && make k8s-install
```

