## Cluster Addons (Layer 3 — on top of K8s)

Four addons deployed — all local, zero cloud accounts:

| Addon | Namespace | Access | Command |
|-------|-----------|--------|---------|
| NGINX Ingress | `ingress-nginx` | `http://localhost:30800` | direct |
| Kubernetes Dashboard | `kubernetes-dashboard` | `https://localhost:8443` | `make dashboard-forward` |
| kube-state-metrics | `medinovai-monitoring` | internal Prometheus feed | — |
| ArgoCD | `argocd` | `http://localhost:8080` | `make argocd-forward` |

**Install all addons**: `make addons-install`  
**Reinstall one**: `make addons-ingress` / `make addons-dashboard` / `make addons-monitoring` / `make addons-argocd`  
**Remove all**: `make addons-uninstall`

### NGINX Ingress Routes (via Host: medinovai.local)

```bash
curl -H "Host: medinovai.local" http://localhost:30800/          # → api-gateway
curl -H "Host: medinovai.local" http://localhost:30800/auth      # → auth-service
curl -H "Host: medinovai.local" http://localhost:30800/clinical  # → clinical-engine
curl -H "Host: medinovai.local" http://localhost:30800/pipeline  # → data-pipeline
curl -H "Host: medinovai.local" http://localhost:30800/notify    # → notification-service
curl -H "Host: medinovai.local" http://localhost:30800/ai        # → ai-inference
```

### ArgoCD GitOps — How It Works

- Watches: `infra/kubernetes/overlays/docker-desktop` on `main` branch
- Every `git push main` → ArgoCD syncs cluster within ~3 minutes automatically
- `selfHeal: true` → manual kubectl edits get reverted to Git state
- `prune: false` → won't auto-delete (safety)
- Check sync status: `kubectl get application medinovai-platform -n argocd`

### Dashboard Token

```bash
# Get token
kubectl -n kubernetes-dashboard get secret medinovai-dashboard-admin-token \
  -o jsonpath="{.data.token}" | base64 --decode
# Or: cat .dashboard-token (gitignored, generated by install-addons.sh)
```

### ArgoCD Password

```bash
kubectl -n argocd get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret \
  -o jsonpath="{.data.password}" | base64 --decode
```

### Kubernetes Dashboard — Namespace Gotcha

Docker Desktop's built-in Kubernetes UI only shows the `default` namespace. Switch the namespace dropdown to see `medinovai-services`, `medinovai-ai`, `ingress-nginx`, etc. The full Kubernetes Dashboard at `https://localhost:8443` shows all namespaces.

